history.content:
As long as you aren't taking math/calculus-oriented upper divs (especially things like 189, for which 53 is essential) you should be fine.

I still recommend taking it early though. 53 presents some beautiful mathematical concepts that blew my mind and changed the way I viewed things.

children.subject: I don't think any CS upper div, even 189, needs math 53. In 189, the most 53 you use is partial derivatives, which is easy to pick up on the fly. EE126 actually uses more math 53 material so if you plan on taking that, it might be worthwhile to take 53 beforehand.

history.content:
I am a current EECS sophomore and I want to put off taking math 53 until spring senior year. Is this a good idea? I'm just not interested in the subject and would rather start taking more upper div CS courses for now.

Are there any upper div CS courses that require or strongly suggest math 53 as a prerequisite?
history.subject: Math 53 delay till Senior year
